1
00:00:00,767 --> 00:00:06,967
[SOFT TRADITIONAL
MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:06,967 --> 00:00:08,667
<i>What happened to Oliver  and
the others is not your fault.</i>

3
00:00:08,667 --> 00:00:10,333
<i>If you really believe
you're being silenced,</i>

4
00:00:10,333 --> 00:00:12,633
<i>then uncover the truth
before it's too late.</i>

5
00:00:12,633 --> 00:00:13,667
<i> Solve this, Marcus.</i>

6
00:00:13,667 --> 00:00:15,667
<i> For our colleagues.</i>

7
00:00:15,667 --> 00:00:17,233
<i> Where is Father?</i>

8
00:00:17,233 --> 00:00:19,267
<i>He was arrested
and imprisoned.</i>

9
00:00:19,267 --> 00:00:21,233
<i> He is their leader.</i>

10
00:00:21,233 --> 00:00:23,500
<i> They destroyed our community.</i>

11
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:26,567
<i>Why are you interrogating
a high-value suspect</i>

12
00:00:26,567 --> 00:00:27,933
<i> without permission?</i>

13
00:00:27,933 --> 00:00:30,267
<i>My colleagues and I witnessed
the mission take a wrong turn</i>

14
00:00:30,267 --> 00:00:31,467
during the Zamboanga operation.

15
00:00:31,467 --> 00:00:33,267
<i> Turn in your gun and badge.</i>

16
00:00:33,267 --> 00:00:37,333
<i>I'll return these to you
after your suspension.</i>

17
00:00:37,367 --> 00:00:38,767
I'm going to make things right.

18
00:00:38,767 --> 00:00:41,700
<i> I know my father is innocent.</i>

19
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:43,633
<i>Whoever killed Oliver
and the others</i>

20
00:00:43,633 --> 00:00:45,467
<i> is highly trained and skilled.</i>

21
00:00:45,467 --> 00:00:46,667
<i> They won't stop</i>

22
00:00:46,667 --> 00:00:49,100
<i>until they destroy
all the evidence.</i>

23
00:00:49,100 --> 00:00:51,167
I know who their next target is.

24
00:00:51,167 --> 00:00:55,300
<i>They will find a way to take
Datu Rahman from our custody.</i>

25
00:00:55,300 --> 00:00:56,700
<i> If my hunch is right,</i>

26
00:00:56,700 --> 00:00:59,000
<i>they're not transferring him
to secure him,</i>

27
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:00,467
<i>they're going to kill
Datu Rahman.</i>

28
00:01:00,467 --> 00:01:01,667
- [KICK LANDS]
- [GRUNTS]

29
00:01:01,667 --> 00:01:03,300
<i>- Jalil!
- [ZAPPING]</i>

30
00:01:03,300 --> 00:01:04,300
<i> Father!</i>

31
00:01:04,300 --> 00:01:06,033
<i>They are always
one step ahead of us.</i>

32
00:01:06,033 --> 00:01:07,467
<i>They are going to
kill Datu Rahman,</i>

33
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:10,133
<i>and once he's gone,
the truth dies with him.</i>

34
00:01:10,133 --> 00:01:12,133
<i>What were you doing there?
You're still suspended.</i>

35
00:01:12,133 --> 00:01:15,300
<i>I want justice for my
comrades who lost their lives.</i>

36
00:01:15,300 --> 00:01:16,533
<i> They were your men, too.</i>

37
00:01:16,533 --> 00:01:17,467
<i>Or were you part
of their deaths?</i>

38
00:01:17,467 --> 00:01:18,567
<i>- How dare you!
- Alright, sir.</i>

39
00:01:18,567 --> 00:01:20,033
<i>I'll uncover the truth
eventually.</i>

40
00:01:20,033 --> 00:01:21,133
<i>I recovered this
at the location.</i>

41
00:01:21,133 --> 00:01:23,733
<i> They're blaming me
for Datu Rahman's escape.</i>

42
00:01:23,733 --> 00:01:25,300
<i>I'll prove to them
that I'm innocent.</i>

43
00:01:25,300 --> 00:01:29,133
<i>I'll check NLEA's ballistics
data for a match to this bullet.</i>

44
00:01:29,133 --> 00:01:31,167
<i>When they reached
Olivios Street,</i>

45
00:01:31,167 --> 00:01:32,167
<i> they disappeared.</i>

46
00:01:32,167 --> 00:01:33,400
<i>Hold on, pause it.
Zoom in.</i>

47
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:36,200
<i>The footage was looped,
so we can't track them down.</i>

48
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:37,667
<i> This is the area.</i>

49
00:01:38,667 --> 00:01:40,333
<i> I can't be wrong.</i>

50
00:01:40,333 --> 00:01:43,600
<i>Here. This is where
they brought Father.</i>

51
00:01:44,567 --> 00:01:51,567
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

52
00:02:01,067 --> 00:02:08,067
[JALIL RECITING
PRAYER IN ARABIC]

53
00:02:16,233 --> 00:02:18,700
[PRAYER CONTINUES]

54
00:02:18,700 --> 00:02:23,400
[SPEAKING IN TAUSUG]

55
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:30,333
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

56
00:02:35,533 --> 00:02:42,433
[MUSIC TURNS SUSPENSEFUL]

57
00:02:49,333 --> 00:02:50,433
[TIRES SCREECH]

58
00:02:51,467 --> 00:02:58,433
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

59
00:03:13,633 --> 00:03:20,600
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

60
00:03:35,433 --> 00:03:42,433
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

61
00:03:57,633 --> 00:04:04,533
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

62
00:04:19,333 --> 00:04:26,267
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

63
00:04:36,867 --> 00:04:43,833
[MUSIC TURNS TENSE]

64
00:04:59,767 --> 00:05:06,867
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

65
00:05:10,067 --> 00:05:11,800
[BEEPING]

66
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:13,800
He's still there.
Hurry up.

67
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:14,767
Yes, ma'am.

68
00:05:15,933 --> 00:05:17,567
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

69
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:24,533
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

70
00:05:39,633 --> 00:05:46,633
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

71
00:06:01,633 --> 00:06:08,600
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

72
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:23,967
[THUD]

73
00:06:26,633 --> 00:06:33,600
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

74
00:06:47,700 --> 00:06:50,733
- [KICKS LANDING]
- [GRUNTING]

75
00:06:50,733 --> 00:06:52,133
[GRUNTS]

76
00:06:52,133 --> 00:06:53,633
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [GRUNTS]

77
00:06:54,867 --> 00:06:56,600
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [EXCLAIMS]

78
00:06:59,667 --> 00:07:01,500
- [THUD]
- Aah!

79
00:07:01,500 --> 00:07:08,467
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

80
00:07:08,967 --> 00:07:09,967
[KICK LANDS]

81
00:07:11,833 --> 00:07:12,900
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [GRUNTS]

82
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:19,067
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

83
00:07:19,100 --> 00:07:20,533
[BOTH GRUNTS]

84
00:07:20,533 --> 00:07:22,467
[WOOD CLATTERS]

85
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:28,433
[BRAKES SCREECH]

86
00:07:28,433 --> 00:07:30,833
There's his car.
Park over here.

87
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:42,967
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

88
00:07:51,900 --> 00:07:53,033
[GLASS SHATTERS]

89
00:07:54,067 --> 00:07:55,733
- [THUD]
- [JALIL EXCLAIMS]

90
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:05,633
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

91
00:08:05,633 --> 00:08:06,833
- [GRUNTS]
- [GUNSHOT]

92
00:08:10,133 --> 00:08:11,167
You!

93
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:18,100
- [FELIX SHOUTING]
- [FLESH SQUELCHES]

94
00:08:18,100 --> 00:08:19,500
- [BLADE SWOOSHES]
- [JALIL EXCLAIMS]

95
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:22,733
- [KICK LANDS]
- Goddammit...

96
00:08:24,567 --> 00:08:25,933
- Glory to God!
- [GLASS SHATTERS]

97
00:08:28,167 --> 00:08:29,200
Run!

98
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:32,767
I'll shoot you,
you bastard!

99
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:37,967
- Wait, you might hit Marcus.
- What the hell?!

100
00:08:39,933 --> 00:08:46,900
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

101
00:08:52,567 --> 00:08:53,567
Go around!

102
00:08:58,967 --> 00:09:05,933
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

103
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:28,733
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

104
00:09:34,167 --> 00:09:35,133
[GUNSHOT]

105
00:09:36,967 --> 00:09:37,967
[THUD]

106
00:09:42,333 --> 00:09:44,033
[MARCUS PANTING]

107
00:09:44,033 --> 00:09:51,000
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

108
00:09:54,033 --> 00:09:55,267
[WOOD CLATTERS]

109
00:10:12,067 --> 00:10:14,167
- You bastard!
- [GUNSHOTS]

110
00:10:14,167 --> 00:10:15,600
- Hurry!
- Stop!

111
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:16,900
[GUNSHOTS]

112
00:10:16,900 --> 00:10:18,200
- [GUNSHOT]
- Come on!

113
00:10:20,233 --> 00:10:21,700
- [MARCUS] That's enough!
- [LARA] Gun down!

114
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:23,167
Gun down!

115
00:10:23,167 --> 00:10:24,867
- Don't shoot him!
- Why not?

116
00:10:24,867 --> 00:10:27,200
- He's a wanted criminal!
- Gun down!

117
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:28,733
We need him alive.

118
00:10:29,867 --> 00:10:32,833
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYS]

119
00:10:35,733 --> 00:10:38,300
He's getting away! Let's go!

120
00:10:38,300 --> 00:10:39,700
Let's go after him!

121
00:10:53,900 --> 00:10:56,667
- [LARA] This way! Hurry!
- [MARCUS] Let's go!

122
00:10:56,867 --> 00:10:59,933
- [OMAR] Hurry!
- Jalil! Let's go! Hurry!

123
00:11:02,900 --> 00:11:05,833
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

124
00:11:21,333 --> 00:11:23,233
Someone helped him escape.

125
00:11:23,767 --> 00:11:25,067
[TIRES SCREECH]

126
00:11:26,333 --> 00:11:27,733
[FELIX] Damn it!

127
00:11:28,100 --> 00:11:29,367
Let's go after them.

128
00:11:30,100 --> 00:11:32,100
- [LARA] Come on!
- I should've killed him.

129
00:11:32,100 --> 00:11:33,233
Lara!

130
00:11:34,100 --> 00:11:36,700
Sorry, this is an
official police operation.

131
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:40,300
- Hurry up!
- It is what it is, sir!

132
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:41,900
[CHUCKLES]

133
00:11:49,433 --> 00:11:50,467
[GASPS]

134
00:11:50,467 --> 00:11:51,833
What happened to you?

135
00:11:53,033 --> 00:11:54,100
Uncle!

136
00:11:54,467 --> 00:11:56,933
- Jalil is shot!
- What?

137
00:11:57,267 --> 00:11:58,633
Oh, dear.

138
00:11:59,767 --> 00:12:01,067
[GROANS IN PAIN]

139
00:12:01,300 --> 00:12:03,167
Hurry up, Uncle!

140
00:12:07,300 --> 00:12:10,267
- Come on!
- I'm coming!

141
00:12:13,267 --> 00:12:14,767
Perfect timing!

142
00:12:15,967 --> 00:12:17,033
Let's go!

143
00:12:17,033 --> 00:12:20,300
You're interfering
with official police operations.

144
00:12:20,700 --> 00:12:22,100
Just get in, Lara.

145
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:25,000
The more we argue about it,
the further he gets away.

146
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,133
Fine!

147
00:12:30,867 --> 00:12:33,833
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

148
00:12:39,733 --> 00:12:41,033
Who's that guy?

149
00:12:41,033 --> 00:12:44,933
I first saw him on the island
when we arrested Datu Rahman.

150
00:12:45,333 --> 00:12:48,800
I saw him again when Datu Rahman
was taken from the streets.

151
00:12:50,233 --> 00:12:52,000
[EXHALES] Could he be...

152
00:12:52,867 --> 00:12:54,033
Do you mean,

153
00:12:54,367 --> 00:12:56,100
he was supposed
to let Datu Rahman escape,

154
00:12:56,100 --> 00:12:58,067
but the kidnappers
got to him first?

155
00:12:58,767 --> 00:13:01,367
It's possible that Datu Rahman
and that guy are in cahoots

156
00:13:01,367 --> 00:13:04,167
with gun smuggling
on the island.

157
00:13:04,500 --> 00:13:07,233
Maybe that's why
they're after you, brother.

158
00:13:09,267 --> 00:13:10,367
Yeah.

159
00:13:11,433 --> 00:13:13,467
But none of it's confirmed.

160
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:16,867
We need to find him
to find out the truth.

161
00:13:17,867 --> 00:13:20,100
[LINE RINGS]

162
00:13:20,100 --> 00:13:21,467
I need you to find someone.

163
00:13:25,433 --> 00:13:26,567
There they go.

164
00:13:26,567 --> 00:13:29,567
Uncle!
Let's take him to the hospital!

165
00:13:29,567 --> 00:13:32,233
[WEAKLY] N-no. Not the hospital.

166
00:13:32,233 --> 00:13:36,467
I know they're required
to report gunshot wounds,

167
00:13:36,467 --> 00:13:38,467
but I can't heal you up!

168
00:13:38,467 --> 00:13:40,467
You need a doctor!

169
00:13:40,467 --> 00:13:42,367
I trust you, Jamilah.

170
00:13:50,133 --> 00:13:51,367
Where did they go?

171
00:13:52,300 --> 00:13:53,500
Chill out.

172
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:56,033
We'll get to them soon.

173
00:13:58,300 --> 00:13:59,967
[LINE RINGS]

174
00:13:59,967 --> 00:14:01,467
Forensics,
this is Agent Angeles.

175
00:14:01,467 --> 00:14:03,800
I need the
facial composite, urgent.

176
00:14:05,933 --> 00:14:08,900
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

177
00:14:20,933 --> 00:14:23,867
[TENSE MUSIC RESUMES]

178
00:14:24,933 --> 00:14:25,900
Good.

179
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:30,500
Let's proceed to Barangay Surga.

180
00:14:31,300 --> 00:14:32,933
The Muslim community?

181
00:14:37,133 --> 00:14:38,200
Omar!

182
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:39,933
Help me! Hurry!

183
00:14:41,133 --> 00:14:43,933
[OMAR] Carry him out!

184
00:14:43,933 --> 00:14:45,467
What happened?

185
00:14:45,467 --> 00:14:48,433
It's a long story.
Bring him to the house.

186
00:14:48,633 --> 00:14:50,500
- And keep quiet.
- We will.

187
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:52,500
[OMAR]
I'll hide the car out back.

188
00:14:53,467 --> 00:14:55,467
Careful. Watch his feet.

189
00:14:55,867 --> 00:14:56,833
He's wounded...

190
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:06,167
[WOMAN] What happened?

191
00:15:06,167 --> 00:15:07,867
- [SHUSHES]
- Don't shout.

192
00:15:11,900 --> 00:15:15,433
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

193
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:20,667
- Hurry up!
- Oh, dear!

194
00:15:20,667 --> 00:15:22,467
What happened to him?

195
00:15:23,333 --> 00:15:25,967
[NORHANA]
Jalil, you're bleeding a lot!

196
00:15:26,867 --> 00:15:27,867
[JAMILAH] Jalil!

197
00:15:29,300 --> 00:15:30,833
[NORHANA] Allah!

198
00:15:32,367 --> 00:15:37,300
I can give him first aid,
but I can't take the bullet out.

199
00:15:37,333 --> 00:15:38,367
[OMAR] Help me with this.

200
00:15:38,367 --> 00:15:41,400
Can't we take him
to the hospital?

201
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:42,667
We can't!

202
00:15:42,667 --> 00:15:45,367
But he's losing so much blood!

203
00:15:45,367 --> 00:15:48,200
- He's in critical condition!
- [JAMILAH] Jalil!

204
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:50,333
[CRYING]

205
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:52,000
Jalil!

206
00:15:53,033 --> 00:15:54,667
Hold on, Jalil!

207
00:15:55,900 --> 00:15:58,900
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

208
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:23,267
Jalil!

209
00:16:23,633 --> 00:16:25,233
Hold on.

210
00:16:25,233 --> 00:16:27,467
[NORHANA] Hold on, Jalil.

211
00:16:27,467 --> 00:16:29,400
Mister Omar! Mister Omar!

212
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:31,067
- Mister Omar.
- What is it?

213
00:16:31,067 --> 00:16:33,533
Mister Omar,
there are cops outside!

214
00:16:33,533 --> 00:16:34,600
[NORHANA] What?!

215
00:16:35,233 --> 00:16:37,367
Thank you. Keep the door shut.

216
00:16:38,633 --> 00:16:40,233
We need backup.

217
00:16:41,767 --> 00:16:44,933
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYS]

218
00:16:50,633 --> 00:16:53,600
The cops
are going to find Jalil!

219
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:54,933
I know!

220
00:16:55,133 --> 00:16:56,967
Where can we hide him?

221
00:16:56,967 --> 00:16:58,333
Hold on...

222
00:16:58,333 --> 00:17:00,267
[NORHANA] Jalil...

223
00:17:00,267 --> 00:17:02,133
[JAMILAH CRYING]

224
00:17:02,133 --> 00:17:03,500
I know!

225
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:05,500
I know a doctor. A good one.

226
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:07,267
Call her!

227
00:17:07,267 --> 00:17:09,167
Allahu akbar...

228
00:17:09,167 --> 00:17:11,133
- Jalil!
- [OMAR] Allahu akbar...

229
00:17:12,767 --> 00:17:15,700
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

230
00:17:29,633 --> 00:17:31,400
Where are we going?

231
00:17:31,667 --> 00:17:34,433
Barangay Surga, I heard.

232
00:17:34,767 --> 00:17:36,067
What?

233
00:17:36,633 --> 00:17:38,267
How's that possible?

234
00:17:38,267 --> 00:17:40,733
I know people there.
It's a quiet place.

235
00:17:43,767 --> 00:17:46,767
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

236
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:02,767
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

237
00:18:03,233 --> 00:18:04,533
Where's the backup?

238
00:18:05,067 --> 00:18:06,333
They're on their way.

239
00:18:08,300 --> 00:18:11,800
Marcus, I'll let you join in,
but not as an SID.

240
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:15,700
You're an observer.
You'll help us ID the person.

241
00:18:16,167 --> 00:18:17,333
Do you understand?

242
00:18:17,667 --> 00:18:18,767
Copy.

243
00:18:25,333 --> 00:18:27,333
We need to be careful here.

244
00:18:27,567 --> 00:18:29,233
There are too many civilians.

245
00:18:29,233 --> 00:18:31,300
We can't put them in danger.

246
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:33,333
[CHUCKLES]

247
00:18:34,767 --> 00:18:37,733
[MUSIC TURNS TENSE]

248
00:18:54,733 --> 00:18:57,700
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

249
00:19:07,433 --> 00:19:10,100
<i> Jalil, you're bleeding a lot!</i>

250
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:13,100
<i>Can't we take him
to the hospital?</i>

251
00:19:13,100 --> 00:19:14,233
<i> We can't!</i>

252
00:19:14,233 --> 00:19:17,567
<i>The cops will find out
that he's still alive.</i>

253
00:19:17,567 --> 00:19:19,733
<i> You'll help us ID the person.</i>

254
00:19:19,733 --> 00:19:21,467
<i> We need to be careful here.</i>

255
00:19:21,467 --> 00:19:22,600
<i> There are too many civilians.</i>

256
00:19:22,600 --> 00:19:24,267
<i> We can't put them in danger.</i>

257
00:19:24,267 --> 00:19:27,233
<i>I'll let you join in,
but not as an SID.</i>

258
00:19:27,233 --> 00:19:28,200
<i> You're an observer.</i>

259
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:30,767
<i>Mister Omar!
There are cops outside!</i>

260
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:32,500
<i> - Keep the door shut.
- Omar!</i>

261
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:35,133
<i>The cops
are going to find Jalil!</i>

262
00:19:35,133 --> 00:19:36,567
<i> Where can we hide him?</i>

263
00:19:40,600 --> 00:19:42,267
<i> We want no harm.</i>

264
00:19:42,267 --> 00:19:44,267
<i>We're here because
we're looking for a suspect.</i>

265
00:19:44,267 --> 00:19:45,733
<i> Do you know this man?</i>

266
00:19:46,233 --> 00:19:47,433
<i> Ask everybody.</i>

267
00:19:47,433 --> 00:19:48,767
<i> And keep your eyes peeled.</i>

268
00:19:48,767 --> 00:19:50,233
<i> Do you know anything?</i>

269
00:19:50,233 --> 00:19:51,433
<i> Come on, Usman.</i>

270
00:19:51,767 --> 00:19:53,667
<i> Why did you bring them here?</i>

271
00:19:53,667 --> 00:19:54,800
<i> We're looking for someone.</i>

272
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:55,933
<i> You're a Muslim.</i>

273
00:19:55,933 --> 00:19:58,267
<i>You know
we don't harbor criminals.</i>

274
00:19:58,267 --> 00:19:59,467
<i> Do you recognize this man?</i>

275
00:19:59,467 --> 00:20:02,767
Is there anyone we can talk to?
<i> A chief or a captain?</i>

276
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:04,600
<i>Yes, Omar.
He lives in that house.</i>

277
00:20:05,633 --> 00:20:07,500
<i> Approach with caution.</i>

278
00:20:10,433 --> 00:20:12,233
<i> What do we do?</i>

279
00:20:15,300 --> 00:20:17,800
<i>You won't be in trouble
if you cooperate with us.</i>

280
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:19,800
<i> I won't let that happen!</i>

281
00:20:20,800 --> 00:20:22,633
<i> Jalil!</i>

282
00:20:24,267 --> 00:20:27,233
[THRILLING MUSIC PLAYS]
